{
  "title": "Beat Bank",
  "children": [
    {
      "title": "Overview",
      "lines": [
        "~450 fixed drum",
        "patterns across 24",
        "genres. No randomness.",
        "",
        "Beat Bank is a MIDI FX",
        "drum sequencer. It",
        "loops the pattern you",
        "pick and plays the",
        "sound generator in the",
        "same slot (e.g. an SF2",
        "drum kit), using GM",
        "drum notes."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "How to use",
      "lines": [
        "In a chain slot:",
        " - Sound generator: a",
        "   drum kit (SF2, or a",
        "   sampler like MrDrums",
        "   with a preset kit).",
        " - MIDI FX: Beat Bank.",
        "",
        "Menu: Pattern, Globals,",
        "Swap.",
        "",
        "Pattern opens a grid",
        "view. Genre-first:",
        " - jog: cycle beats in",
        "   the current genre",
        " - knob 1: switch genre",
        " - knob 2: swing",
        " - knob 3-8: change the",
        "   pad/note of each row",
        "It shows the grid, the",
        "pad each drum drives,",
        "and which knob edits it.",
        "Click/Back exit. Loops",
        "when Move plays.",
        "",
        "Globals: Swing + Note",
        "Map (also on knob 2 /",
        "in the Pattern view)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Change Pads",
      "lines": [
        "In the Pattern view the",
        "knobs re-point each drum",
        "voice to a different pad",
        "(drumrack) or note (gm),",
        "live while you audition.",
        "",
        "Knobs are positional:",
        " K3 = 1st row, K4 = 2nd,",
        " .. up to K8 (6th row).",
        "Rows are in fixed order",
        "(kick, snare, hats, then",
        "extras), so a voice",
        "keeps its pad across",
        "patterns; only which",
        "knob reaches it moves.",
        "",
        "Each row shows its knob",
        "(K3..) and the pad it",
        "hits. Handy for matching",
        "a MrDrums kit without",
        "leaving Beat Bank. Edits",
        "save with the slot;",
        "switching Note Map",
        "resets them."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Note Map",
      "lines": [
        "Sets which MIDI notes",
        "the drums use:",
        "",
        " gm - full General MIDI",
        "  drum map. Use with",
        "  SF2 / soundfont kits.",
        "",
        " drumrack - all notes",
        "  in 36-51, the Move",
        "  drum-rack range. Use",
        "  with MrDrums and",
        "  other pad samplers.",
        "",
        "Default is drumrack",
        "(most drum synths). Only",
        "switch to gm for SF2.",
        "",
        "Cowbell/Conga/Perc only",
        "sound in drumrack mode",
        "on 36-51 samplers."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Recording",
      "lines": [
        "Record the Schwung way:",
        "Shift+Sample (Quantized",
        "Sampler) resamples the",
        "chain's audio to a WAV",
        "in Samples/Schwung/.",
        "",
        "No Move-track mixing -",
        "it stays in Schwung."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Add Your Own",
      "lines": [
        "Patterns are plain",
        ".beat text files. Drop",
        "your own in:",
        " UserData/schwung/",
        "  beatbank/patterns/",
        "",
        "See _HOWTO.txt there",
        "for the format."
      ]
    }
  ]
}
